anchise based in milwaukee wisconsin along with marc lasry he also owns the league of legends team flyquest  contents  career  fortress investment group  springleaf financial services  nationstar  milwaukee bucks  personal life  references careeredit edens received a bs in finance and business administration from oregon state university in  he began his career in  at lehman brothers where he was a partner and managing director until  he then went to black rock blackrocks private equity division blackrock asset investors and was there until  as a partner and managing director fortress investment groupedit wes edens was one of five principal partners—peter pete briger jr robert rob kauffman randal randy nardone and michael edward mike or novo novogratz—who founded fortress investments in  edens investment style was described in a  the wall street journal article as one based on contrarian bets creative financing and a knack for building business from investments fortress became the first publicly traded buyout firm on february   with eden and his partners taking the company public through its initial public offering fortress had sold an  share to the public for  million by  by  fortress assets under management included both private equity and publicly traded alternative investment vehicles—fourteen private equity funds four hedge funds and two real estate vehicles and went public when the japanese financial holding company nomura holdings acquired  of fortress for  million in december  with proceeds going to the five principals edens and his partners became paper billionaires edens became cochairman of the board of directors at fortress in  and helped the company which saw its stock price fall to below one dollar after the subprime mortgage crisis resurge by offering subprime lending he served as chairman of fortress transportation and infrastructure investors llc from  to may  in january  fortress announced the creation of an esports professional video gaming team called flyquest the team currently has a league of legends team that competes in the north american league of legends championship series na lcs springleaf financial servicesedit edens who runs fortress’s private equity business was the catalyst at fortress behind the purchase of subprime lender springleaf financial services—then known as aigs american general finance which made fortress the springleafs majority stakeholder by  the value of springleaf holdings inc had ballooned to  billion — putting the firm’s gain at more than  times fortress’s original investment of  million in  edens was heralded as the new king of subprime lending by the wall street journal edens is chairman of the subprime lender springleaf financial services—formerly known as aigs american general finance fortress acquired  of springleaf in august  for  million and used springleaf and nationstar to build out a financialservices business within its privateequity unit which manages  billion in assets nationstaredit edens is chairman of nationstar mortgage formerly known as centex home equity company llc a subprime home equity mortgage lender which was acquired by fortress for  million in  in  centex was operating in major us markets in  states and delivered more than  homes in the united states in  edens connection to nationstar mortgage was cited by opponents of a proposed publicfinancing deal for the construction of a new arena the wisconsin entertainment and sports center they advocated for more public resources to rehabilitate foreclosed homes managed by nationstar milwaukee bucksedit in  edens and marc lasry purchased the bucks from herb kohl for  million promising to keep the team in wisconsin and build a new arena to replace the bmo harris bradley center personal lifeedit edens and his wife lynn have four children youngest daughter mallory received significant controversial media attention following her appearance as the milwaukee bucks team representative at the  nba draft lottery his hobbies include horse jumping and mountain climbing referencesedit  a b milwaukee bucks president and owner herb kohl introduces new team ownership and announces  million gift for arena milwaukee bucks april   retrieved july     alumni business partner award winners announced corvallis oregon  retrieved december     a b fortress investment grpcl a fignew york wesley robert edens bloomberg  retrieved december     wesley edens forbes october    a b mclean bethany april  over the hedge vanity fair retrieved september     company overview of fortress investment group llc bloomberg december   retrieved december    information and data displayed in this profile are created and managed by sp global market intelligence a division of sp global  gregory zuckerman henny sender and scott patterson february   hedgefund crowd sees more green as fortress hits jackpot with ipo the wall street journal retrieved december   cs maint uses authors parameter link  clark patrick  fortress chieftain mike novogratz wrestles with olympians youth…and wall street new york observer retrieved    a quick buck    nomura to acquire minority stake in fortress investment group pdf tokyo and new york fortress investment group december   retrieved december     about fortress  wesley r edens retrieved august     a b c zuckerman gregory august   meet the new king of subprime lending fortress investment’s wesley edens turns  million into  billion ‘it’s not a bad thing’ retrieved december   on wall street the best way to get over a losing trade is to bounce back with a winner mr edens is enjoying a surprising whopper subprime loans  the giant gains have helped offset recent stumbles by fortress in its “macro” hedgefund business—and made mr edens the new subprime king  httpwwwbizjournalscommilwaukeenewsmilwaukeebuckscoownerwesedensventuresintohtml  a b c matthew monks and devin banerjee october   fortress wins big in turnaround of subprime lender springleaf retrieved december   cs maint uses authors parameter l